SUBSTITUTE FOR
HOUSE BILL NO. 5711
A bill to amend 2008 PA 295, entitled
"Clean and renewable energy and energy waste reduction act,"
by amending the title and sections 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 61, 101,
173, and 191 (MCL 460.1001, 460.1003, 460.1005, 460.1007, 460.1009,
460.1011, 460.1013, 460.1061, 460.1101, 460.1173, and 460.1191),
the title and sections 1, 3, 5, 7, 9, 11, 13, 173, and 191 as
amended and section 101 as added by 2023 PA 235 and section 61 as
added by 2016 PA 342; and to repeal acts and parts of acts.
THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF MICHIGAN ENACT:
1 TITLE
2 An act to require certain providers of electric service to
3 establish and recover costs for renewable energy and clean energy
4 programs; to require certain providers of electric or natural gas
RMH H02431'25 (H-3) cxb0i8

2
1 service to establish, and recover costs for, energy waste reduction
2 programs; to ensure that any energy cost savings from renewable
3 energy, clean energy, and energy waste reduction programs are
4 ultimately returned to customers; to authorize the use of certain
5 energy systems to meet the requirements of those programs; to
6 provide for the approval of energy waste reduction service
7 companies; to reduce energy waste by state agencies and the public;
8 to create a wind energy resource zone board and provide for its
9 power and duties; to authorize the creation and implementation of
10 wind energy resource zones; to provide for expedited transmission
11 line siting certificates; to provide for customer generation and
12 net metering programs and the responsibilities of certain providers
13 of electric service and customers with respect to customer
14 generation and net metering; to provide for fees; to prescribe the
15 powers and duties of certain state agencies and officials; to
16 require the promulgation of rules and the issuance of orders; to
17 authorize the establishment of residential energy improvement
18 programs by providers of electric or natural gas service; to
19 authorize certification by this state before the construction of
20 certain wind and solar energy facilities and energy storage
21 facilities; to regulate certain local ordinances; and to provide
22 for civil sanctions, remedies, and penalties.
23 Sec. 1. (1) This act may be cited as the "clean and renewable
24 energy and energy waste reduction act".
25 (2) The purpose of this act is to promote the development and
26 use of clean and renewable energy resources and the reduction of
27 energy waste through programs that will cost-effectively do all of
28 the following:
29 (a) Diversify the resources used to reliably meet the energy
RMH H02431'25 (H-3) cxb0i8

3
1 needs of consumers in this state.
2 (b) Provide greater energy security through the use of
3 indigenous energy resources available within this state.
4 (c) Encourage private investment in renewable energy. and
5 energy waste reduction.
6 (d) Coordinate with federal regulations to provide improved
7 air quality and other benefits to energy consumers and citizens of
8 this state.
9 (e) Provide more reliable and resilient energy supplies during
10 periods of extreme weather.
11 (3) Pursuant to In accordance with the reconciliation
12 processes provided for in this act, the commission shall determine
13 the costs and savings resulting from compliance with the former
14 renewable energy , program and the former clean energy , and energy
15 waste reduction programs program required under this act and
16 include those costs and savings in the determination of the rates
17 charged to customers of the electric and natural gas providers.
18 This section does not prohibit the commission from authorizing
19 shared savings or incentive programs as provided for in this act.
