4 Sec. 61. An electric provider shall offer to its customers the
5 opportunity to participate in a voluntary green pricing program
6 under which the customer may specify, from the options made
7 available by the electric provider, the amount of electricity
8 attributable to the customer that will be renewable energy. If the
9 electric provider's rates are regulated by the commission, the
10 program, including the rates paid for renewable energy, must be
11 approved by the commission. The customer is responsible for any
12 additional costs incurred and shall accrue any additional savings
13 realized by the electric provider as a result of the customer's
14 participation in the program. If an electric provider has not yet
15 fully recovered the incremental costs of compliance, both of the
16 following apply:
17 (a) A customer that receives at least 50% of the customer's
18 average monthly electricity consumption through the program is
19 exempt from paying surcharges for incremental costs of compliance.
20 (b) Before entering into an agreement to participate in a
21 commission-approved voluntary green pricing program with a customer
22 that will not receive at least 50% of the customer's average
23 monthly electricity consumption through the program, the electric
24 provider shall notify the customer that the customer will be
25 responsible for the full applicable charges for the incremental
26 costs of compliance and for participation in the voluntary
27 renewable energy program as provided under this section.
